Eight people were injured in a crash involving a taxi and car near Blair Atholl on Monday, emergency medical services reported this week.
Rescue Care paramedics said in a statement that they had responded to the call and arrived on scene just after 4pm.
It had been established at the time that more ambulances and advanced life support units needed to be dispatched to the scene as multiple patients were found to be injured.
READ: Three injured in taxi accident
Once all eight patients had been stabilised, they were transported to various Durban hospitals for further medical  care. The victims had sustained injuries varying from minor to serious.
They said that the taxi and car had collided on the M13, Pinetown bound near Blair Atholl in Westville on Monday afternoon. 
"At this stage the exact cause of the collision is unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further."
The Mercury
